OL,3,CMum's plea to PM over 'Postcode
OL,4,Clottery' of care for dying children
OL,6,FA bereaved mother has implored the
OL,7,FPrime Minister to act after she had to
OL,8,Fbattle to get round-the-clock care at
OL,9,Fhome for her son in his final days.
OL,11,FClare Buchanan's son Oliver, 11, died
OL,12,Ffrom a brain tumour in 2023. She said
OL,13,Fshe knew Oliver needed to be at home
OL,14,F"for as long as possible" but was told
OL,15,Fthat that it would be "very difficult"
OL,16,Fto put a care package in place for
OL,17,Fthis to happen.
OL,19,FMs Buchanan has written to Sir Keir
OL,20,FStarmer, saying that many families
OL,21,Ffeel "abandoned and overwhelmed".
